      <h1 style="margin-top:14px">PhilHealth &amp; the cost of dialysis</h1>
      <p class="lead">The question everyone's afraid to ask — answered as plainly as we can.</p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Please note:</strong> the exact figures below are placeholders until Dr. Rivero
        confirms what St. John Biocare is comfortable publishing. Coverage rules and case rates
        can change — we'll keep this page current.
      </div>

      <h2>Does PhilHealth cover dialysis?</h2>
      <p>Yes. PhilHealth provides a dialysis benefit for eligible members, paid as a “case rate” per session up to an annual number of sessions. Bring your Member Data Record (MDR) and we'll help you check what applies to you.</p>

      <h2>What is a “case rate”?</h2>
      <p>A case rate is a fixed amount PhilHealth pays per covered session. If the session cost is within that amount, your out-of-pocket cost can be very low. We'll always explain any difference before your treatment.</p>

      <h2>What will I actually pay?</h2>
      <p>It depends on your membership status, remaining covered sessions, and the specific services you need. We'll sit with you and go through the real numbers for your situation — no surprises.</p>

      <p style="margin-top:20px"><a href="/new-patients#request" class="btn btn--primary">Ask us about your coverage</a></p>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:20px;font-size:.9rem">Medically and administratively reviewed. Last updated: 2026. We never overstate coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
